author: Clemence Michallon For Dailymail.Com
title: Kaila Prins says burlesque helped her anorexia recovery | Daily Mail Online
text: 'I don't have to look a certain way to be seen': Former anorexic and exercise addict tells how burlesque and POLE dancing finally healed her body image after years of battling eating disorders Kaila Prins, 30, became obsessed with calories and running in high school Struggled with disordered eating through college and as a grad student Became a bodybuilder, then tried vegan and paleo diets but nothing stuck It wasn't until she tried burlesque and pole dancing that she really recovered 'It took the fear away of having a body and having it be out of control,' she said
